.TH LOOPY 1 "February 2026" "loopy 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
loopy \- Neo4j load generator for testing database performance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B loopy
[\fIGLOBAL OPTIONS\fR]
.B COMMAND
[\fICOMMAND OPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Loopy is a comprehensive Neo4j load testing tool that generates configurable workloads to test database performance. It supports various operation types, configurable threading, and detailed performance reporting.

.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help information and exit
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version  
Show version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIFILE\fR
Configuration file path (default: config.properties)
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-neo4j\-uri " " \fIURI\fR
Neo4j connection URI (default: bolt://localhost:7687)
.TP
.BR \-U ", " \-\-username " " \fIUSER\fR
Neo4j username (default: neo4j)
.TP
.BR \-P ", " \-\-password " " \fIPASSWORD\fR
Neo4j password (interactive prompt if not provided)
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-threads " " \fINUM\fR
Number of worker threads (default: 4)
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-duration " " \fISECONDS\fR
Test duration in seconds (default: 300)
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-write\-ratio " " \fIRATIO\fR
Write operation ratio, 0.0-1.0 (default: 0.7)
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-batch\-size " " \fINUM\fR
Batch size for operations (default: 100)
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Quiet mode - minimal output
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose mode - detailed output

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B run
Execute load test (default behavior). Runs the main load testing operation with configured parameters.
.TP
.B validate
Validate configuration file without running the test. Checks configuration syntax and connectivity.
.TP
.B benchmark
Run predefined benchmark scenarios. Execute standardized performance tests for comparison.
.TP
.B test\-connection
Test Neo4j connectivity and perform diagnostics. Verify database connectivity and permissions.
.TP
.B setup
Interactive setup wizard for guided configuration creation. Step-by-step configuration generation.
.TP
.B config
Configuration management commands with subcommands:
.RS 7
.TP
.B init
Generate default configuration file
.TP  
.B validate
Validate configuration file syntax and values
.TP
.B show
Display current effective configuration
.TP
.B edit
Open configuration file in default editor
.RE
.TP
.B tune
Performance tuning and optimization commands:
.RS 7
.TP
.B \-\-show\-profiles
Display available load profiles (light, medium, heavy, stress)
.TP
.B \-\-profile " " \fIPROFILE\fR
Show details for specific load profile
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-tune
Analyze system and provide optimization recommendations
.RE
.TP
.B report
Generate detailed reports from test results:
.RS 7
.TP
.B \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: html, markdown, or csv
.TP
.B \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Output file path
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic load test with default settings:
.B loopy run

.TP  
Quick 30-second test with 2 threads:
.B loopy run --duration 30 --threads 2

.TP
Interactive setup wizard:
.B loopy setup

.TP
Test database connectivity:
.B loopy test-connection --quick

.TP
Generate configuration file:
.B loopy config init

.TP
Show performance tuning profiles:
.B loopy tune --show-profiles

.TP
Generate HTML report:
.B loopy report --format html --output results.html

.TP
High-intensity load test:
.B loopy run --threads 16 --duration 600 --write-ratio 0.8 --batch-size 2000

.SH CONFIGURATION
Loopy uses a properties file for configuration. The default location is \fIconfig.properties\fR in the current directory. Configuration files support the following properties:

.TP
.B Neo4j Connection
neo4j.uri, neo4j.username, neo4j.password
.TP
.B Load Testing Parameters  
threads, duration.seconds, write.ratio, batch.size
.TP
.B Data Configuration
node.labels, relationship.types, property.size.bytes
.TP
.B Reporting
report.interval.seconds, csv.logging.enabled, csv.logging.file

.SH LOAD PROFILES
Loopy includes predefined load profiles for different testing scenarios:

.TP
.B light
2 threads, 100 batch size, 30 seconds, 30% writes - for development testing
.TP
.B medium  
4 threads, 500 batch size, 120 seconds, 50% writes - for staging environments
.TP
.B heavy
8 threads, 1000 batch size, 300 seconds, 70% writes - for production testing
.TP
.B stress
16 threads, 2000 batch size, 600 seconds, 80% writes - for stress testing

.SH REPORTING
Loopy can generate detailed reports in multiple formats:
.TP
.B HTML reports
Rich, interactive reports with charts and detailed metrics
.TP
.B Markdown reports  
Text-based reports suitable for documentation
.TP
.B CSV exports
Raw data suitable for analysis in spreadsheet applications

.SH FILES
.TP
.I config.properties
Default configuration file
.TP
.I loopy-results.csv
Default CSV output file (when CSV logging enabled)
.TP
.I ~/.loopyrc
User-specific configuration file

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B LOOPY_NEO4J_URI
Default Neo4j connection URI
.TP
.B LOOPY_USERNAME
Default Neo4j username  
.TP
.B LOOPY_PASSWORD
Default Neo4j password
.TP
.B LOOPY_CONFIG_FILE
Default configuration file path

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error (configuration, connection, or runtime error)
.TP  
.B 2
Command line argument error

